body:
12x03

I’m rewatching The Foundry, episode 12x03, and it’s so so good. I know a lot of people hate Mary, and I know that late seasons Crowley was pretty disappointing, but this episode is so good.

We have:

  • Grumpy and sarcastic Cas
  • Mary being so done with not being listened to.
  • Crowley making jokes
  • Rowena being a badass
  • Mary being a badass
  • Cas making jokes
  • Sam and Dean arguing because Sam knows what’s up and Dean’s in denial.
  • Dean being so happy that his mom is with him.
  • Bacon
  • So much Cas. Did I mention he’s in this episode? Like, a lot?
  • Agent Beyonce (oh yeah, that’s Cas)
  • There’s even a little Destiel! “Mornin, sunshine. Want some coffee?”

I dunno this is turning out to be one of my favorite episodes.

summary: When Good Omens gets released I’m going to sit in front of my TV with a blanket over my head and a dangerous array of snackfoods...
body:
When Good Omens gets released I’m going to sit in front of my TV with a blanket over my head and a dangerous array of snackfoods and binge it all at once.

My stomach will regret it but my unending enthusiasm for this ridiculous work of fiction will not.

summary: Still more GO collab: Turn In Your Arms
title: Still more GO collab: Turn In Your Arms
body:
by @irisbleufic & @procrastinatingbookworm

#5 / 8: SATURDAY, 23 AUGUST 1997

[Tam Lin retelling; rated M.  Updates daily till done.  This update’s come a little faster than it might have otherwise because some of you are delightfully impatient.]

*

After reluctantly leaving Crowley’s flat the day before, Aziraphale hadn’t been sure Crowley would come by—whether he would consider their need for a meeting fulfilled or not.

But arrive he did, and would have been right on time if he’d come a day earlier. He carried a glossy hardcover in one hand and a bottle of Château Lafite Rothschild’s finest in the other.

“They’ve scarcely bounced back from the phylloxera,” Crowley said apologetically, handing both book and wine to Aziraphale, “so this vintage might be subpar. The book’s just a convenient find. Said you liked my organizational methods, so how about my research?”

Aziraphale took that—and the way Crowley pushed his glasses into his hair—as sufficient apology. He lingered over the way Crowley smiled and bit his lip, the flash of one sharp eye-tooth unmistakably coy.

summary: It's In His Kiss
title: It's In His Kiss
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2TdcJmD

by MandalaRose

“Dean,” Cas says, straightening from his position against the wall. “I’m sorry if that kiss made you uncomfortable earlier. That wasn’t my intention.”
Direct and to the point, that’s Cas. It’s a trait Dean usually appreciates, he likes knowing where he stands with the man, but right now it’s making him decidedly uneasy. Cas is right of course, the kiss did make Dean uncomfortable, just not for the reasons the other hockey player thinks. As per usual, Dean covers his discomfort with bravado and sass.
“Nah, I wasn’t uncomfortable,” he lies. “Besides, you call that little peck a kiss? I hate to break it to you buddy, but Edith the octogenarian kissed better than that.”
Cas looks momentarily annoyed with Dean’s obvious deflection, but then his expression clears and he steps into Dean’s space before cocking his head and narrowing his eyes, “Are you criticizing my kissing abilities, Dean?”

Popular hockey player, Dean Winchester, has a habit of finding himself on the arena’s Kiss Cam during games, usually while standing next to a devoted fan. But what’ll happen when the person next to him ends up being his teammate, best friend, and secret crush, Cas Krushnic?

summary: GO collab halfway-point update: Turn In Your Arms
title: GO collab halfway-point update: Turn In Your Arms
body:
by @irisbleufic & @procrastinatingbookworm

#4 / 8: FRIDAY, 22 AUGUST 1997

[Tam Lin retelling; rated M.  Updates daily till done.]

*

Crowley tipped sidelong, twisting with improbable swiftness, arms locking around Aziraphale’s shoulders. He buried his face in Aziraphale’s neck, his labored breath hot as a brand.

Aziraphale froze for a moment before gathering Crowley close. He clung tightly in turn, bowing his head. How insincere his prayers had been, and how undeserving of the answer in his arms.

summary: Crowley’s name
title: Crowley’s name
body:
I was thinking today about the way people pronounce Crowley’s name and why that speaks to his name change. When I first read the book in my mind I read his name like it rhymed with crowd. Then when I saw the ads for the series I realised it was supposed to be crow like the bird. 

Until that moment I could never really understand the significance of the name change. However when you look at Crawley as a name you know it’s supposed to be a reference to his snake form/ crawling on the ground. Crow on the other hand means to brag or exult. To crow is a matter of pride.  

I feel like Crowley changing his name was a matter of taking ownership of himself and choosing a name that fit who he ‘as a person’ was.
